@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Registration"
@prev "About"

                        Installation

     Just copy the drawer wherever you want it, and you're ready to go. Make
sure you have CanDo.library (version 2.511) in your LIBS: directory. 
     I advise keeping all the files in the same drawer as your data file
("pres.data") will be saved to the same drawer as the main program.
     The files are:

     *    Database_Rx
     *    Database_Rx.info
     *    Database_Rx.Guide
     *    Database_Rx.Guide.info

@endnode

@node "Registration" "Registration"
@next "Future"
@prev "Installation"

                        Registration

     Database_RX V1.0 is giftware. If you like it, find any bugs, have any
suggestions, or whatever, please drop me a line to focal@interport.net or
monday21@delphi.com. If I see enough interest in this program, I will release
the updated version with more features.

                        @{" Future" link "Future" 0}
@endnode

@node "Future" "Future"
@next "Bugs"
@prev "Registration"

                         Future

     If there is enough of a response ( see @{"Registration" link "Registration" 0} ), I will release an
updated version with some new features. Such as:

     *    A feature to store doctors' telephone numbers.
     *    A feature to store pharmacy names & numbers.
     *    Dosage information
     *    Whether or not generic.
     *    Cost.
     *    Perhaps an extension to store individual user information,
               such as allergies, doctors, discounts, etc.

If you'd like to see these features, or have other suggestions, please let me
know. Thanks! :)
@endnode

